	<exercise xml:id="class_motion-warmup">
		<title>Warm-up</title>
		<p>
			Is the average speed of the upper object greater than, less than, or equal to the average speed of the lower object?  
			Explain your reasoning.
		</p>
	</exercise>

	<exercise xml:id="class_ball-in-the-air">
		<title>The Ball in the Air</title>
		<p>
			
		</p>
		<p>
			Imagine throwing  a ball straight into the air.  
			<ol>
				<li>
					Describe the motion in words (use complete sentences).
				</li>
				<li>
					Identify any quantities of interest by symbol.
				</li>
				<li>
					Draw a motion diagram for the ball.
				</li>
				<li>
					Discuss any assumptions or idealizations you want to make.
				</li>
			</ol>
		</p>
<p>
			Estimate the average velocity of the ball:
			<ol>
				<li>
					During the entire motion
				</li>
				<li>
					During the first half of the motion
				</li>
				<li>
					During the second half of the motion
				</li>
			</ol>
		</p>
		<p>
			Do you think it would be appropriate or necessary to use a calculator for this activity?
		</p>
	</exercise>



